<exercise checkit-seed="2982" checkit-slug="P4" checkit-title="Random Variables">
  <statement>
      
      <p>
          Consider store that sells primarily PC's.  Each customer that comes in may buy one, none or several PC.  Let <m>X</m> denote   the number of PCs a customer who comes into the store purchases.  Consider the following probability distribution table for <m>X</m>.
      </p>
      
      <p>
          <me>
              \begin{array}{|c
              |c
              |c
              |c
              |c
              |
              }
              
              \hline
              X_i 
              &amp; 0
              &amp; 1
              &amp; 2
              &amp; 3
              \\
              \hline
              P(X=X_i)
              &amp; 0.508
              &amp; 0.396
              &amp; 0.092
              &amp; ???
              \\
              \hline
              \end{array}
          </me>
      </p>
      
      
      <p>
          <ol>
              <li>
                  What is the value of the missing entry?
              </li>
              <li>
                  Find the expectation of <m>X</m>, <m>E(X)</m>,  and interpret what it means in context of this problem.
              </li>
              <li>
                  Find variance of <m>X</m>, <m>Var(X)</m>.
              </li>
              <li>
                  Find the standard deviation of <m>X</m>, <m>\sigma_X</m>.
              </li>
          </ol>
          
      </p>
      
      
     
      
          
          
          
          
      
  </statement>
